reviews.review_text:
The rating is based on how great sounding it is imho... Went poking around for something never listened to and stumbled onto this, a great sounding AUD to these ears, nice and full, all the instruments being heard loudly and clearly enough with just enough audience to make me feel like I'm standing and dancing somewhere in the venue with them. It really "sounds" like the taper got really lucky with the environment around where he was set up, most excellent in that regard.

As to the performance itself it sounded solid enough to these ears though nothing earth shattering. Felt it was a pretty inventive setlist for its time with neat little touches, the 1/2 Step>Franklin's>Stranger was the 1st, only to happen three more times and the Don't Ease>Promised Land only happened once more as far as I could tell and you can hear them having a bunch of fun with the pairing, Brent tearing into the B-3 on both of them. Ultimately happy that I gave this a spin, thanks to anybody/everybody that had a hand in this recording!
